# TypeScript Standards

## `type` vs `interface`

| Use case | Keyword |
|----------|---------|
| React component props | `interface` — supports `extends` |
| Data shapes (DTOs) | `type` — immutable contracts |
| Function signatures | `type` — union/intersection support |
| Discriminated unions | `type` — variant types |
| Config objects | `type` — more composable |
| Module augmentation | `interface` — required by TS |

```typescript
// ✅ interface for props
interface ButtonProps extends BaseProps {
  onClick: () => void
  variant: 'primary' | 'secondary'
}

// ✅ type for data, functions, unions
type User = { id: string; email: string }
type Handler = (data: Data) => Promise<void>
type Result<T> = { ok: true; value: T } | { ok: false; error: Error }
```

## Never use `any` — use `unknown` + type guards

```typescript
// ❌ AVOID
function handle(value: any) { ... }

// ✅ DO
function handle(value: unknown) {
  if (typeof value === 'string') { /* safely narrowed */ }
}

// ✅ Type guard pattern
function isUser(v: unknown): v is User {
  return typeof v === 'object' && v !== null &&
    typeof (v as Record<string, unknown>).id === 'string'
}
```

## Error handling — type guards, not casts

```typescript
// ❌ AVOID
const err = error as { message: string }

// ✅ DO
if (error instanceof Error) {
  console.error(error.message)
}
```

## Type assertions — honest types + runtime validation

```typescript
// ❌ AVOID — blind cast hides missing values
const { email } = (await req.json()) as { email: string }

// ✅ DO — include undefined, then validate
type Body = { email: string | undefined; password: string | undefined }
const body = (await req.json()) as Body
if (!body.email?.trim()) throw new Error('Invalid input')
```

## `satisfies` over `as` for validated inference

```typescript
// ❌ AVOID — bypasses validation
const config = { timeout: 'fast' } as Config  // no error!

// ✅ DO — validates AND preserves literal types
const config = { endpoint: '/api', timeout: 5000 } satisfies Config
```

## `as const` for readonly literals

```typescript
const STATUS = { OK: 200, NOT_FOUND: 404 } as const
type StatusCode = typeof STATUS[keyof typeof STATUS]  // 200 | 404
```

## Explicit return types on all exported functions

```typescript
// ✅ Required for all exports
export function fetchUser(id: string): Promise<User | null> { ... }
export async function createPost(data: PostInput): Promise<Post> { ... }
```

## Discriminated unions — exhaustive handling

```typescript
type ApiState<T> =
  | { status: 'idle' }
  | { status: 'loading' }
  | { status: 'success'; data: T }
  | { status: 'error'; error: Error }

// Always handle ALL variants in switch or if/else chains
```

## Generics — constrain and provide defaults

```typescript
// ✅ Constrained
function pick<T extends object, K extends keyof T>(obj: T, key: K): T[K]

// ✅ Default type parameter
type QueryResult<TData, TError = Error> =
  | { status: 'loading' }
  | { status: 'success'; data: TData }
  | { status: 'error'; error: TError }
```
